reviews.text:
service was amazing and fast and amazing place looks great to study and really clean
but the egg mayo croissant is awful how do u mess up a croissant like that
putting so many fibrous grains on the croissant that keep on dropping when i eat (annoying sia) is lowkey gross like i can tell itâ€™s trying too hard to be healthy till itâ€™s unpractical to eat and tastes like trash.
also the egg mayo inside is disgusting itâ€™s more of a over peppered tasteless piece of mushed omelette like literally all i taste is the pepper pieces and the pepper pieces are so big u can hear the crunch itâ€™s awful

Love the vibes here, and as an NUS student who takes caffeine as life, I always welcome any coffee place on campus with study facilities (like big tables and plugs and wifi). So itâ€™s usually quite productive IF I am able to find seats. And during sem time, probability is very low, maybe 10% chance if you come in the afternoon. And as expected, everyone here stays for long hours.

Question to NUS FM/OSL: do students who donâ€™t get Starbucks get to sit here? I mean I get this is school compound and in general, all students can sit at any open space to mug. But I see more than half of the students sitting here not getting a Starbucks drink. Many times I buy a Starbucks drink and I had to go elsewhere to sit :( first come first serve > buying a drink at Starbucks?

The Starbucks is located at the third level of the Technoedge building, which houses the Technoedge canteen.

It has some seating spaces both indoor and outdoor. It offers all the standard offerings found in any other Starbucks stores.
